@Node RegisterPrompt "Register!"

Please @{"Register" link Register} HydraBBS, doing so will remove this annoying prompt!

Since HydraBBS has been released NOBODY has registered it yet!

I *cannot* continue to work on HydraBBS if no-one registers it, as I
have to keep the aminet and the web-site upto date which involves
long phone calls (Internet isn't free in the UK!)  ISP charges (for
an ISP that provides cgi-bin and SSI's) Electricity Bills, and
hardware maintenence.

I know for a fact that several people are running it as their
primary BBS now (having converted from an old system) which requires you
to register it.

If no-one registers it within the next two weeks (from the day that
V1.08 is released) I shall add nag requesters and a timeout, and maybe some
key files.  I know I said I'd never do this, but situations change.

HydraBBS is *really* cheap to register, and is a very easy process.

Also, people who register HydraBBS get the full source code to it, as
well as their own personal area on the main HydraBBS site.

So, @{" Register NOW " link Register}

@{" Click here to continue to the main menu" link MainMenu}


@EndNode

